place.name: OXWICK
place.gazetteerText: OXWICK, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; 4 miles S by W of Fakenham r. station. Post-town, Litcham, under Swaffham. Acres, 719. Real property, with Pattesley, £1, 883. Pop. of O. alone, 66. Houses, 14. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £234. Patron, E. Blake, Esq. The church is old; and consists of nave and chancel, with bell-turret. Charities, £9. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
